HEADWORD: Warye
<hw>War"ye</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wergian</ets>, <ets>wyrgean</ets>. Cf. <er>Worry</er>.]</ety>
<def>To curse; to curse; to execrate; to condemn; also, to vex.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <altsp>[Spelled also <asp>warrie</asp>,
<asp>warry</asp>, and <asp>wary</asp>.]</altsp> ⟦ldquo⟧Whom I thus blame
and <xex>warye</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

